               <head>Grant; Needham Street, etc.; 1302-1303</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Needham-Street)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate notBefore="1302" notAfter="1303">1302-1303</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Beuelers</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Persoun</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105432">Moulton (Multone)</placeName>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Persoun">
                           <forename>Beatrice</forename> his wife</persName>, for a certain sum of money, of half the lands and tenements held by him in the parish of <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gaysle)</placeName>, with a messuage in the vill of Nedham, lying next to the messuage of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Berelowe</surname></persName>, abutting on the highway and lying next to the <placeName type="street" key="place_113013">Derenyngge road</placeName>; of the land in the crofts, 3.5 acres lie at the upper part next to the land of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperlyng</surname></persName>, abutting on the said Walter's messuage; half an acre lies in another croft, next to William Sperlyng's land, and abutting on his messuage; 1.5 acres lie on <placeName type="minor">Gayslehel</placeName>, next to the land of William Sperlyng, abutting at both ends on the land of the <persName>Earl of Gloucester</persName>; 1 acre lies in <placeName type="minor">Heynhowe</placeName> next to the land of William Sperlyng, abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) 'Fabri'</surname></persName>; in Merebak lie 1.5 acres, next tot he land of William Sperlyng, and abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Crystemasse</surname></persName>; in <placeName type="minor">Punchefeld</placeName> lie 3 acres at the upper part next to the land of William Sperlyng, and abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Humfrey</forename> of <surname>Lacforde</surname></persName>; in <placeName type="minor">Wytefeld</placeName> lie 3.5 acres at the upper part, next to the land of William Sperlyng, and abutting on the highway; in <placeName type="minor">Weyercroft</placeName> lies half an acre next to the land of William Sperlyng, and abutting on the highway; half an acre in the same lies next tot he land of William Sperlyng, abutting in land of Walter Persoun; 2.5 acres lie next to the land of William Sperlyng, and abut on <placeName type="minor">Suht Heth</placeName>; one acre, next to and abutting on the land of the same; in <placeName type="minor">Karemere</placeName> lie 1 acre and 1 rood, next to the land of William Sperlyng, adn abutting on 'Karemere pettes'; in <placeName type="minor">Hauedlond</placeName> lies half an acre next to the land of William Sperlyng, and abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) 'Fabri'</surname></persName>; in <placeName type="minor">Mereback</placeName> lies 1 rood next to 'le felde weye', abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Kersoner</surname></persName>. With these lands is the right of foldage bought from <persName>
                           <forename>Alexander</forename> le <surname>Beneler</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gaysle)</placeName></persName>, in the fields of <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gaysle)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, and <placeName key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteford)</placeName>.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName> on Monday [11 March] before the feast of St Gregory, Pope. 31 Ed. I [1302-1303].
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Warner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Crystemasse</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Aumener</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperke</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Kersoner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> le <surname>Warde</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de la <surname>Berewe</surname></persName>, and many others.
                     The seal is wanting. 
                     Endorsed: Joh' Beueller: fald'.
                     </p>
